{"cursor":"16340","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox company |name = Gallup |logo = |caption = The Gallup, Inc. world\nheadquarters in Washington, D.C. The National Portrait Gallery can be seen in\nthe reflection. |type = |foundation = |founder = George Gallup |location_city =\nWashington, D.C. Omaha, Nebraska |location_country = U.S. |location =\n|locations = |key_people = |industry = |products = |production = |services =\n|revenue = |operating_income = |net_income = |aum = |assets = |equity = |owner =\nJim Clifton |num_employees = |parent = |divisions = |subsid = |homepage =\n[http://gallup.com/ Gallup.com] |footnotes = |intl = }}\n\n'Gallup, Inc.', is primarily a research-based, global performance-management\nconsulting company. Originally founded by George Gallup in 1935, the company\nbecame famous for its public opinion polls, which were conducted in the United\nStates and other countries. Gallup works with major businesses and organizations\naround the world. http://www.businessweek.com/articles/2012-11-08/right-or-wrong-\ngallup-always-wins\n\nIn 1988, 4 years after Gallup died, Selection Research (SRI) purchased it from\nits heirs. SRI wanted the Gallup name to use on its polls, which gave them more\ncredibility and higher response rates. Today the poll is used to gain\nvisibility. Some of Gallup's key practice areas are employee engagement,\ncustomer engagement, talent management, and well-being.\n\nGallup has nearly 40 offices in more than 20 countries. http://www.gallup.com/strategicconsulting/EN-\nUS/UniquelyGallup.aspx?ref=global http://www.gallup.com/corporate/115-\n/about-gallup.aspx?ref=f World headquarters are in Washington, D.C.\nOperational headquarters are in Omaha, Nebraska. Its current Chairman and CEO is\nJim Clifton.\n\nThere are about 2,000 employees in the privately held company, working in four\ndivisions: Gallup Poll, Gallup Consulting, Gallup University, and Gallup\nPress. Ira Boudway, \"Right or Wrong, Gallup Always\nWins, Bloomberg BusinessWeek Nov. 12, 2012\n","linknr":243,"url":"The_Gallup_Organization","recorded":1375080321,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Gallup_(company)&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Gallup_(company)&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Gallup_(company)","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=The_Gallup_Organization&redirect=no","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Gallup_International_Association","/wiki/File:Gallup_Portrait.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2f/Gallup_Portrait.jpg/160px-Gallup_Portrait.jpg","/wiki/Washington,_D.C.","/wiki/National_Portrait_Gallery_(United_States)","/wiki/George_Gallup","/wiki/Washington,_D.C.","/wiki/Omaha,_Nebraska","/wiki/United_States","http://gallup.com/","/wiki/Performance_management","/wiki/Consulting_(disambiguation)","/wiki/George_Gallup","#cite_note-1","#cite_note-2","#cite_note-3","/wiki/Washington,_D.C.","/wiki/Omaha,_Nebraska","/wiki/Nebraska","#cite_note-autogenerated1-4","#History","#Gallup.27s_Polling_in_the_United_States","#Methodology","#Accuracy","#Gallup.27s_Global_Polling","#Methodology_2","#Alleged_violations_of_the_False_Claims_Act_and_the_Procurement_Integrity_Act","#See_also","#References","#Further_reading","#External_links","/w/index.php?titl